# Skill Authoring Rules

## Required Frontmatter
Every SKILL.md must have these fields:
```yaml
---
name: skill-name
version: "1.0.0"
description: >
  Trigger description — be specific about WHEN to use this skill.
  Include example phrases. Be slightly pushy (Claude undertriggers).
allowed-tools: Read, Grep, Glob
---
```

## Paired Agent Definition
Every skill must have a matching `agents/<name>.json`. If you create a new skill, create the agent JSON too. The `"skill"` field in the JSON is what wires the skill content into orchestrator execute mode.

## Body Limits
- Keep SKILL.md body under 500 lines
- If approaching limit, move reference content to `references/` subdirectory
- Reference files from SKILL.md with explicit "when to read" guidance

## Trigger Description
The `description` field is the ONLY thing Claude sees when deciding whether to invoke a skill. Make it:
- Specific about input patterns and contexts
- Include example user phrases
- Cover edge cases and near-misses

## Version Bumping
Increment `version` when:
- Behavior changes meaningfully
- New sections added
- Trigger description updated

Format: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH (semver, strings only)

## Progressive Disclosure
Three loading levels:
1. `name` + `description` — always in context
2. SKILL.md body — loaded when skill triggers
3. `references/` files — loaded only when explicitly needed

Structure content for this hierarchy.
